ode>import torch\nimport torch.cuda\nimport torch.nn as nn\nfrom torch.autograd import Variable\n\nx = torch.FloatTensor(16, 30)\nlinear = nn.Linear(30, 20)\n\ny = linear(Variable(x))\ny_target = torch.FloatTensor(16, 20)\n\nloss = nn.MSELoss()\ndef hook(layer, grad_input, grad_output):\n    return grad_input * 2\nloss.register_backward_hook(hook)\n\nerr = loss(y, Variable(y_target))\nerr.backward()\n</code></pre>\n<p>removing <code>loss.register_backward_hook(hook)</code> resolves it</p>", "body_text": "import torch\nimport torch.cuda\nimport torch.nn as nn\nfrom torch.autograd import Variable\n\nx = torch.FloatTensor(16, 30)\nlinear = nn.Linear(30, 20)\n\ny = linear(Variable(x))\ny_target = torch.FloatTensor(16, 20)\n\nloss = nn.MSELoss()\ndef hook(layer, grad_input, grad_output):\n    return grad_input * 2\nloss.register_backward_hook(hook)\n\nerr = loss(y, Variable(y_target))\nerr.backward()\n\nremoving loss.register_backward_hook(hook) resolves it", "body": "```\r\nimport torch\r\nimport torch.cuda\r\nimport torch.nn as nn\r\nfrom torch.autograd import Variable\r\n\r\nx = torch.FloatTensor(16, 30)\r\nlinear = nn.Linear(30, 20)\r\n\r\ny = linear(Variable(x))\r\ny_target = torch.FloatTensor(16, 20)\r\n\r\nloss = nn.MSELoss()\r\ndef hook(layer, grad_input, grad_output):\r\n    return grad_input * 2\r\nloss.register_backward_hook(hook)\r\n\r\nerr = loss(y, Variable(y_target))\r\nerr.backward()\r\n```\r\nremoving `loss.register_backward_hook(hook)` resolves it"}